\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The issue with equations is maddening for all LaTeX novices.
 After preparing a beautiful, elaborate formula, the user is dismayed to
 find that, in the pdf output, the equation overflows into the margins and
 off the page.
 It is just a (frustrating) fact of life.
 LaTeX does not enforce line breaks within equations, so equations can run
 off the edge of the page, or, in this case outside the edges of the column.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Short equations are going to come out fine, as in 
